snippet.textDisplay:
Firstly, For me it’s being myself - I have big anxiety problems and self confidence and I want to start perceiving me as myself and not be something I’m not, and I’m response I feel like if I open myself and show my true colours people will follow and see me as almost an inspiration.

Secondly, for me it’s getting back on horses. I have practically grown up on horses but this summer I had a very bad accident and was lucky to come away from it able to walk, it’s been tricky for me to get back on horses but I wana push myself in 2020 and get past this setback.

Thirdly, I want to conquer my mental health which has been troubling me for the past 1.5 years. I have been seeing a councillor for 1 year and that has helped enormously but recently have had my first two sessions with a psychologist. By the end of 2020 I wana be able to lift my head hi and just say I’m happy again.

snippet.textDisplay: Ok so to me seeking discomfort in 2019 has meant moving out from my parent's house right after graduating from high school and turning 18 to go to Argentina for a year. I want learn from the people in a Villa (poor neighborhood) of Tucumán (smallest provincia of Argentina) and confront myself with my priviledges (which is something that REALLY discomforts me) through volunteer work. I know that this may sound kind of stereotypical but it really is something that challenges me a lot. Yesterday I was able to spend a absolutely unforgettable christmas Party with a befriended family from here and today I'm leaving for my first ever  solo trip. What scares me the most is being alone. I'd be lying if I said that it isn't hard or wouldn't  make me doubt myself a lot but Yeah, seeking discomfort is real.
